In the INTEREST OF: M.K.M. Juvenile Officer, Respondent,
v.
M.K.M., Appellant. WD 81792 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: July 16, 2019 Lori Fluegel, Kansas City, MO, Attorney for Respondent. Craig A. Johnston, Assistant State Public Defender, Columbia, MO, Attorney for Appellant. Before Division Two: Thomas N. Chapman, Presiding Judge, and Mark D. Pfeiffer and Cynthia L. Martin, Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

M.K.M. ("Juvenile") appeals from the order of adjudication of the Circuit Court of Jackson County, Missouri, Family Court Division, finding that the Juvenile Officer proved beyond a reasonable doubt that Juvenile committed acts that would constitute the felony of sodomy in the first degree if committed by an adult. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. We affirm. Rule 84.16(b).
